I found the immediate bug: the clone inherits a checkpoint hook, so using `MIM` as collateral reverts. I’m pulling the real collateral and fork setup now.
Plan update
The revert comes from `PrivilegedCheckpointCauldronV4.addCollateral()`: the deployed clone calls `collateral.user_checkpoint(to)`, so setting collateral to `MIM` makes `cook(ACTION_ADD_COLLATERAL,...)` revert. The fix needs to use the target cauldron’s actual checkpoint collateral and source a dust amount of it via realistic public liquidity.
